definition.value: Segment of lymphatic tree organ which consists of branching sets of lymphatic vessels with or without interspersed lymph nodes; together with other lymphatic trees (organ part), it constitutes a lymphatic tree (organ). Examples: subclavian lymphatic tree, bronchomediastinal lymphatic tree, intestinal lymphatic tree.
